    topic: "Infectious Disease",
    subtopic: "Silicosis and Tuberculosis",
    stem: `A 57-year-old man presents to your GP practice with progressive cough, fever and malaise for the past 3 months. His background history includes smoking for 20 years and working in pottery industry for 30 years. Five years ago, he developed shortness of breath, for which he sought medical care and was diagnosed with silicosis. Which one of the following can be the cause for his recent condition?`,
