    topic: "Infectious Disease",
    subtopic: "Urinary tract infection in pregnancy",
    stem: `A 24-year-old woman, 19 weeks pregnant, presents to your office complaining of frequency, urgency and dysuria. Further investigations establish the diagnosis of urinary tract infection. The culture results are still pending. The patient has a history of allergic reactions to penicillin, manifesting as a rash. Which of the following is the antibiotic of choice for her treatment?`,
