    topic: "Infectious Disease",
    subtopic: "Infective endocarditis - HACEK group",
    stem: `Based on the culture results of a 42-year-old man with infective endocarditis, hemophilus ducreyi is found to be the causative organism. He is treated with a course of intravenous ceftriaxone. Which one of the following would be the most appropriate investigation in addition to treatment?`,
