    stem: `A 30-year-old woman who is 34 weeks pregnant presents with dysuria and frequency. On examination, her temperature is 37.3°C. There is no nausea, vomiting, flank pain, or tenderness. A urine dipstick test is positive for nitrites and leucocytes. A mid-stream urine sample is sent for culture and sensitivity. Meanwhile, which antibiotic is most appropriate for empiric therapy in this woman?`,
