    topic: "Infectious Disease",
    subtopic: "Cryptococcal meningitis in immunocompromised host",
    stem: `A 21-year-old girl is brought to the emergency department with headache and mild neck stiffness. She had kidney transplantation last year. Examination of cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) reveals a cell count of 150 with 70% monocytes. CSF glucose level is 1.2 mmol/L and protein 1.8 g/L. Which one of the following investigation is most important to consider for this patient?`,
