    stem: `Jarred, three years old, was brought to your clinic by his mother with a complaint of a non-healing abscess in his neck. It started with a painless lymph node enlargement in the left submandibular area, which gradually developed into an abscess over a few weeks. A 5-day course of oral amoxicillin prescribed by another doctor failed to treat the abscess. Which of the following would be the most appropriate management of this condition?`,
