    topic: "Infectious Disease",
    subtopic: "IV cannula-related bacteremia",
    stem: `Melany, 75 years old, was admitted to the hospital 5 days ago after she was diagnosed with bacterial community acquired pneumonia. She was started on intravenous antibiotics with a desirable therapeutic response and feeling much better. On her 5th day admission, she suddenly develops a high fever of 39.5°C, chills, and rigors. Which one of the following could be the most likely explanation to this clinical picture?`,
