    topic: "Public Health",
    subtopic: "Relative risk calculation",
    stem: `In a randomized controlled trial (RCT) conducted to study the effect of aspirin on prevention of coronary artery events among diabetic smokers, the results in the two arms of the study are as follows: ASA group: 1 coronary event, 99 no coronary event; Placebo group: 2 coronary events, 98 no coronary event. Which one of the following is the relative risk of not using ASA?`,
