    subtopic: "Vaccination and febrile seizures",
    stem: `Tom, 18 months of age is brought to your general practice for vaccination. Today, he has a runny nose and fever of 38.1°C but otherwise is doing well and healthy. He had an episode of febrile seizure 7 months ago when he had an upper respiratory tract infection. Which one of the following vaccine is best to not be given to him today?`,
