    stem: `John is 72 years old and a regular patient of yours in your GP clinic. He has depression and has been treated for that a few times. He also smokes 15-20 cigarettes a day and drinks alcohol in moderation. He is in the clinic today and wants to quit smoking. Which one of the following would be the most important option to consider for him to assist his quitting?`,
