    stem: `A 60 year-old man presents to your clinic for a routine medical check-up. He smokes 45 cigarettes a day, and drinks 10 standard drinks daily. He has a body mass index (BMI) of 32 kg/m². He wears seat-belt almost 60% of the times when he drives. He is motivated to follow lifestyle modification advice. Which one of the following is the most significant advice for prevention of cardiovascular disease and premature death in this patient?`,
