    id: "ph-amedex-0073",
    topic: "Public Health",
    subtopic: "Smoking cessation in pregnancy",
    stem: `A 29-year-old woman presents to your clinic at 14 weeks pregnancy for consultation regarding smoking cessation. She tried to give up smoking when she found out she is pregnant but she failed. She is worried about her baby's wellbeing and wants to quit smoking. Which one of the following is the most appropriate management option for her?`,
