    id: "ph-amedex-0085",
    topic: "Public Health",
    subtopic: "Absolute Cardiovascular Risk Assessment",
    stem: `A 72-year-old man presents to your practice for assessment. He does not smoke and has no history of diabetes mellitus or cardiovascular disease. On examination, he has a blood pressure of 172/100 mmHg, confirmed with a second reading. On blood tests, he has a total cholesterol level of 6.2 and HDL of 1mmol/L. According to the following chart which one of the following is his absolute cardiovascular risk?`,
