    explanation: `This patient is a 37-year-old man with a family history of melanoma (father diagnosed 8 months ago) but with only benign nevi on examination and no personal history of melanoma or atypical nevi. He has multiple benign nevi which is a risk factor for melanoma, but the presence of benign nevi alone does not warrant excision. The most appropriate management is to reassure him and advise opportunistic skin checks. This allows for regular monitoring without unnecessary interventions, while maintaining awareness of his increased risk due to family history. Referral to a dermatologist would be more appropriate if he had atypical nevi or other concerning features. Regular scheduled reviews at specific intervals (12 months or 2-5 years) are less flexible than opportunistic checks, which can be done whenever he visits for other reasons.`,
